---
Title: A Line Too Long For The Page
Author: Lyrical
Year: 2026
PForm: Freeform
---
@@poem:start
Some verse lines run on far past what a narrow chapbook column can hold,
+so the overflow is marked as a continuation, not a new line of its own.
It keeps the original line's number and its own hanging indent.

A short line needs no marker at all.
@@poem:end

~>The Editors, 2026
